review_blob: lightly hopped and weak on the palate, if you were to give it to me blindfolded I would say it tastes like Foster's lager with a kick.  But oh what a kick... some of my glory days were spent in the Philipines with this beer in the sunshine, and it therefore has sentimental value.  This beer has the alchol kick to take you to the next level, and do it quickly.  Good memories, good times, and better than american bud/coors/miller swill

Overwhelming pungeant citrus aroma, and the palate does not dissapoint from the nose.  Powerful hop aroma and flavor with the malt perfectly balancing by dripping like caramel arount the hops.  Possibly the worlds most perfect beer, if you love hops.
